   FBN-PREVIEW-VIOLENCE (Undated) _ Doctors, team trainers and NFL
executives say that the level of violence on the football field is
at an all-time high. Concussions, shoulder and knee injuries,
ripped ligaments, popped tendons, and even cases of paralysis are
at record numbers. Collisions are literally tearing players apart.
By Mike Freeman. 2500 words.
