three Groucho steps beginning with your left foot, hop on your
third step (on your left foot). Pump the arms as you Groucho-walk
and then swing them wider or shoot them overhead, as in basketball,
when you hop. Continue to step-step-step-shoot (on the count of 1,
2, 3, 4).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Backward Groucho Walking Uphill  &LR; . . . Be sure the way is clear
of debris. Crouch low into the knees (however, avoid bending too
low and putting stress on the knee) and Groucho-walk up the hill
backward.
</P>
<P>
   How-to-Walk Book No. 9: ``Walk It Off! 20 Minutes a Day to
Health and Fitness'' by Suzanne Levine, D.p.m. (Plume/Penguin,
1990, 257 pages)
</P>
<P>
   Sample Walking Type: The Sensual Stroller . . . For this one,
think Marilyn Monroe or Elvis Presley. Your whole body is alive
with pleasure as you walk. You feel your lithe limbs moving under
your clothes. You step forward with a slinky roll, leading with
your hips, your arms gracefully flowing forward and back with each
sensuous unfolding of your thighs.
</P>
<P>
   You move like a graceful tiger, leisurely but calculating. . . .
You're beautiful and desirable, and you know it. You're humming
something provocative, like ``Mama Said There'd Be Days Like This''
or ``The Girl From Ipanema.'' You know you look marvelous. You're
in the mood for love.
</P>
<P>
   How-to-Walk Book No. 10: ``Walk Yourself Thin'' by David A.
Rives (Moon River, 1998, 149 pages)
</P>
<P>
   Quote: First of all, it really is a fact of life: If you're
going to get thin, you're going to have to control  &UR; something! &LR;  If
you don't want to control the amount you eat, then you're going to
have to control the amount you exercise. There's no getting around
it.
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh, poop!''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Postscript: Perhaps walking isn't for you. In that case, you might
consider books like ``The Art of Breathing'' by Nancy Zi (Vivi,
1997), or even ``The Art of Doing Nothing'' by Veronique Vienne
(Clarkson Potter, 1998), which includes chapters on lounging,
napping and yawning.  &LR;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
