<SLUG> BC-BBN-McGWIRE-TV-LADN </SLUG>
 
FOX L.A. AFFILIATE TO FINALLY AIR McGWIRE 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Fox's Los Angeles affiliate, KTTV-Channel 11,
promises to have today's 1 p.m. network coverage of Mark McGwire's
attempt to tie the major league single-season home run record _
unlike what the station did Saturday when McGwire had three shots
at matching it.
</P>
<P>
   Fox Sports, headquartered in Century City, gave its West Coast
affiliates the option of carrying Saturday's St. Louis-Cincinnati
contest as the first part of a TV doubleheader. The regionally
scheduled Dodgers-San Francisco telecast started at 1 p.m., so it
wouldn't have been pre-empted.
</P>
<P>
   Before leaving on Labor Day weekend, KTTV management declined
the option; the Fox affiliate in San Francisco did carry the game.
</P>
<P>
   An employee on the KTTV news assignment desk Saturday said the
station received many calls during the 10 a.m.-to-1 p.m. period but
they were not authorized to do anything about changing the
programming.
</P>
<P>
   When McGwire homered in his first at bat to reach 60, KTTV was
in the midst of showing the ``Mighty Morphin Power Rangers'' kids
show. As McGwire struck out the last three at bats in an attempt to
tie Roger Maris' record of 61, the station aired, as previously
scheduled, ``WMAC Masters'' martial arts show; ``Student Bodies,''
a show for teen-agers, and ``Hangin' With Mr. Cooper'' prior to Fox
Sports's own ``In the Zone'' taped baseball kids show.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
