<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-PENN-ST-MISS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PENN STATE BEATS SOUTHERN MISSISSIPPI, 34-6  
 (HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
   By RON DICKER   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   STATE COLLEGE, Pa. _ Penn State may get to celebrate Coach Joe
Paterno's 300th victory next week, but No. 299 will probably have a
greater impact on the Nittany Lions' confidence. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Penn State began its 33rd season under Paterno Saturday with
muted expectations and unanswered questions.
</P>
<P>
   Would its defense, which collapsed at the end of last season,
turn around? Could its rushing attack be productive despite losing
Curtis Enis to the National Football League and three other backs
to injury or transfer?
</P>
<P>
   And could a No. 1 quarterback emerge, either the dropback-style
Kevin Thompson or the scrambler Rashard Casey? &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For one afternoon, the answers were yes, yes and yes. And the
Nittany Lions, ranked 13th in both the news media and coaches
polls, provided the affirmative against a respected opponent,
cruising to a 34-6 victory over 21st-ranked Southern Mississippi. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Penn State built a 20-0 lead before halftime, allowing the
96,617 fans at Beaver Stadium to concentrate on their suntans and
next week's game against Bowling Green.
</P>
<P>
   That game which should be a coronation for Paterno. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The junior Cordell Mitchell emerged from his understudy's role
to rush for 99 yards on 16 carries. Fullback Omar Easy had 63 yards
and Eric McCoo added 51 yards on 4 carries as the Lions rolled up
255 yards rushing. Thompson showed more poise in Paterno's platoon
setup at quarterback, completing 10 of 15 passes for 140 yards and
a touchdown. Casey completed 3 of 6 for 28 yards. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The Golden Eagles, who have won the Conference USA title two
straight years, were able to move through the air. Quarterback Lee
Roberts connected on 27 passes for 289 yards, breaking Brett
Favre's school record for completions, and receiver Sherrod Gideon
hauled in a school-record 13 receptions for 176 yards. But Southern
Miss stumbled to a miserable 9 yards rushing on 21 attempts. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   At halftime, the Nittany Lions had held the Golden Eagles to
minus-18 yards rushing while amassing 264 total yards on offense
themselves. Midway through the second quarter, Mitchell had already
rushed for 85 yards. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Thompson threw just one pass on Penn State's first scoring
drive, an 8-yarder to Corey Jones that put the Lions at the
Southern Miss 10. Mitchell pushed the Lions to the 1 on two carries
and fullback Mike Cerimele plowed in for the touchdown. After a
29-yard field goal by Travis Forney, Easy ran in from the 5 to give
Penn State a 17-0 lead in the second quarter. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Early in the second half, Eddie Shaw of Southern Miss muffed Pat
Pidgeon's punt and Penn State's Mack Morrison recovered the ball to
set up Joe Nastasi's leaping 12-yard touchdown reception from
Thompson to make it 27-0. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
